entry.tran: (在某一活动上)远远超过，远胜于
entry.def: If you are outclassed by someone, they are a lot better than you are at a particular activity.

example.ex: Mason was outclassed by Lennox Lewis in his tragic last fight at Wembley...
example.tran: 梅森在他悲剧性的最后一场拳击比赛中于文布利惨败给了伦诺克斯·刘易斯。

example.ex: Few city hotels can outclass the Hotel de Crillon.
example.tran: 没有几家城市酒店能与克里雍大饭店媲美。

entry.def: If one thing outclasses another thing, the first thing is of a much higher quality than the second thing.

example.ex: These planes are outclassed by the most recent designs from the former Soviet Union...
example.tran: 苏联的最新产品要远比这些飞机性能优越。

example.ex: The story outclasses anything written by Frederick Forsyth.
example.tran: 这本小说比弗雷德里克·福赛思的所有作品都更为精彩。

means.word_mean: 1. decisively surpassed by something else so as to appear to be of a lower class
